WEBVTT

00:10.749 --> 00:13.230
Narrator: AT THIS MOMENT,
A FATHER AND DAUGHTER

00:13.274 --> 00:16.320
WERE ON A CAMEL TRIP
ACROSS THE RUB' AL-KHALI,

00:16.364 --> 00:18.322
THE 600-MILE-LONG BODY OF SAND

00:18.366 --> 00:23.806
IN THE VAST, HARSH WILDERNESS
KNOWN AS THE ARABIAN DESERT.

00:23.849 --> 00:27.114
IN TRUTH, YOUNG CHUCK
SHOULD HAVE BEEN FLOATING

00:27.157 --> 00:28.506
ON A SEA OF DREAMS,

00:28.550 --> 00:30.813
BUT AT 8 YEARS, 8 MONTHS,
21 DAYS OLD,

00:30.856 --> 00:34.947
SHE WAS KEPT AWAKE
BY THE VARICELLA ZOSTER VIRUS,

00:34.991 --> 00:37.646
ALSO KNOWN AS CHICKENPOX.

00:37.689 --> 00:41.780
HER FATHER, CHARLES CHARLES,
HOPED THIS MAGICAL JOURNEY

00:41.824 --> 00:44.348
WAS THE ANTIDOTE
TO HIS DAUGHTER'S DISCOMFORT.

00:44.392 --> 00:46.568
INDEED, IT EASED THE GIRL'S ITCH

00:46.611 --> 00:50.224
AND REPLACED IT WITH A BURNING
DESIRE FOR ADVENTURE --

00:50.267 --> 00:54.402
ADVENTURES HER FATHER PROMISED
TO TAKE HER ON SOMEDAY.

00:54.445 --> 00:57.970
SADLY, SOMEDAY'S ADVENTURES
WOULD NEVER COME,

00:58.014 --> 01:01.800
FOR, IN A MONTH,
CHARLES CHARLES WOULD DIE,

01:01.844 --> 01:04.064
AND YOUNG CHUCK
WOULD LEARN THE SAD LESSON

01:04.107 --> 01:10.113
THAT, TRY AS ONE MIGHT, ONE CAN
NEVER RECAPTURE WHAT ONCE WAS.

01:10.157 --> 01:13.856
UNTIL CHARLOTTE CHARLES
WOULD AGAIN HAVE HER FATHER.

01:13.899 --> 01:15.075
HELLO.

01:15.118 --> 01:16.554
Narrator:
ONLY HAVING HIM BACK

01:16.598 --> 01:18.600
MEANT LYING
TO THE PIE MAKER SHE LOVED.

01:18.643 --> 01:21.777
When Ned touches you,
you play dead.

01:21.820 --> 01:25.607
SAY, YOU GOT A SQUATTER
IN YOUR OLD DIGS OVER THERE?

01:25.650 --> 01:27.522
HMM?

01:27.565 --> 01:30.264
CHUCK?

01:30.307 --> 01:31.830
I WAS WORRIED.
I THOUGHT --

01:31.874 --> 01:33.093
Charles: CHARLOTTE.

01:33.136 --> 01:34.746
IT'S OKAY, DAD.

01:34.790 --> 01:35.965
"DAD"?

01:41.057 --> 01:42.711
YOU KEPT YOUR FATHER
ALIVE.

01:42.754 --> 01:44.539
THIS LOOKS BAD.

01:44.582 --> 01:46.758
IT IS BAD.
IT'S HORRIBLY BAD.

01:46.802 --> 01:48.238
IT CAN'T BE THAT BAD.

01:48.282 --> 01:50.675
NOT LIKE I'M THE FIRST GHOST
HE'S EVER SEEN.

01:50.719 --> 01:51.981
PLEASE SAY SOMETHING.

01:52.024 --> 01:54.201
Lily:
HE'S UP HERE.

01:54.244 --> 01:55.245
LILY?

01:55.289 --> 01:56.551
QUICK!

01:56.594 --> 01:57.813
NO! GET OUT!

01:57.856 --> 02:00.207
LILY, VIVIAN,
IS THAT YOU?!

02:00.250 --> 02:02.165
YOU KNOW GOOD AND WELL
WHO WE ARE!

02:02.209 --> 02:03.514
DAMN IT!

02:03.558 --> 02:05.037
AND WE ARE
SPITTIN' PISSED

02:05.081 --> 02:07.388
AT BEING SERVED UP
A STEAMING PLATE OF DOOR!

02:07.431 --> 02:09.041
Vivian:
I DON'T GET PISSED.

02:09.085 --> 02:11.566
A GYPSY ONCE TOLD ME
IT BRINGS ON HEMORRHOIDS.

02:11.609 --> 02:13.133
Why can't I just go out there
and talk to her?

02:13.176 --> 02:15.178
Shh! No! After you were gone,
Lily and Vivian

02:15.222 --> 02:17.180
moved into our old house
to look after me.

02:17.224 --> 02:19.356
They can't know
that we're alive again.

02:19.400 --> 02:21.445
But they're your aunts,
button-button.

02:21.489 --> 02:23.491
Except for the one
that's my mother.

02:27.451 --> 02:28.800
SO YOU KNOW.

02:31.760 --> 02:33.501
AND YOU'RE OKAY?

02:34.937 --> 02:36.156
YEAH?

02:36.199 --> 02:38.506
CAN WE GET BACK
TO YOUR RUDE RECEPTION?

02:38.549 --> 02:39.942
SORRY. I THOUGHT
YOU WERE HOME INVADERS.

02:39.985 --> 02:41.335
THEN WHY DID YOU
SAY MY NAME?

02:41.378 --> 02:42.771
-I DIDN'T.
-I HEARD IT.

02:42.814 --> 02:44.207
IT MUST HAVE BEEN
YOUR BAD EYE -- EARS.

02:44.251 --> 02:46.209
WHEN YOU CAME OVER HERE
TO CHECK FOR SQUATTERS

02:46.253 --> 02:47.645
AND DIDN'T IMMEDIATELY
RESURFACE,

02:47.689 --> 02:48.951
LILY ASSUMED THE WORST.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.257
AND BROUGHT
TWO BARRELS OF BACKUP.

02:50.300 --> 02:51.867
HEY, NO SQUATTERS.
NO ANYONE.

02:51.910 --> 02:53.347
LET'S ALL GO HOME.
[ THUD ]

02:53.390 --> 02:54.652
WHAT WAS THAT?

02:54.696 --> 02:55.914
THAT WAS ME.

03:02.878 --> 03:05.228
NO!

03:05.272 --> 03:09.232
OH! OHH!
GET IT AWAY!

03:09.276 --> 03:10.625
[ SOBBING ]

03:10.668 --> 03:12.235
IT'S ALRIGHT.

03:12.279 --> 03:14.977
LILY'S BEEN PETRIFIED OF CLOWNS
EVER SINCE OUR GRANDPAPA

03:15.020 --> 03:17.501
CHASED HER AROUND THE HOUSE
WITH ONE OF THOSE.

03:17.545 --> 03:19.373
Narrator:
IT WAS CHARLOTTE CHARLES

03:19.416 --> 03:21.723
WHOSE STRATEGIC PLACEMENT
OF THE TOY

03:21.766 --> 03:23.812
PREVENTED
HER STRONG-WILLED MOTHER

03:23.855 --> 03:26.597
FROM STRONG-ARMING HER WAY
FURTHER INTO THE CLOSET.

03:35.302 --> 03:37.608
WE NEED TO TALK.

03:37.652 --> 03:42.222
YOU DON'T WANT TO HEAR
WHAT I HAVE TO SAY.

03:42.265 --> 03:45.268
Narrator: A LOW-PRESSURE SYSTEM
MOVING IN FROM THE COAST

03:45.312 --> 03:49.054
THREATENED PAPEN COUNTY
WITH ITS FIRST WINTER STORM.

03:49.098 --> 03:50.578
BUT FOR THE PIE MAKER AND CHUCK,

03:50.621 --> 03:53.537
IT WAS AS IF
THE TEMPEST HAD ALREADY HIT.

03:53.581 --> 03:56.758
IF I WERE THINKING
CLEARER, I'D...

03:56.801 --> 03:58.673
GIVE YOU SPACE
TO PROCESS EVERYTHING,

03:58.716 --> 04:01.066
BUT I HAVEN'T SLEPT
SINCE ALL THIS HAPPENED.

04:01.110 --> 04:03.678
SINCE...
I MADE IT HAPPEN.

04:03.721 --> 04:06.985
IF YOUR DAD'S ALIVE,
SOMEONE ELSE HAD TO DIE.

04:07.029 --> 04:08.248
WHO WAS IT?

04:08.291 --> 04:09.727
DWIGHT DIXON.

04:09.771 --> 04:12.121
WE FOUND HIM WITH A SNIPER RIFLE
IN THE CEMETERY.

04:12.164 --> 04:13.644
WHAT?

04:13.688 --> 04:15.559
EMERSON THINKS THAT
HE WAS PLANNING ON KILLING

04:15.603 --> 04:19.215
BOTH YOU AND ME
THE NIGHT WE RE-ALIVED MY DAD.

04:19.259 --> 04:21.652
EMERSON KNOWS?

04:21.696 --> 04:26.266
HE HELPED ME BURY DWIGHT
IN MY DAD'S EMPTY GRAVE.

04:26.309 --> 04:28.703
HE WANTED ME TO TELL YOU
RIGHT AWAY, BUT I-I BEGGED HIM,

04:28.746 --> 04:32.097
"PLEASE, JUST WAIT
UNTIL I KNOW WHAT TO SAY."

04:32.141 --> 04:34.665
AND THEN...YOU...

04:34.709 --> 04:35.840
YOU FOUND ME FIRST.

04:35.884 --> 04:37.451
WHAT WOULD HAVE HAPPENED
IF I DIDN'T?

04:37.494 --> 04:38.843
I'D HAVE
BROUGHT YOU UP HERE

04:38.887 --> 04:41.281
AND TOLD YOU THAT I WAS
RECKLESS AND SELFISH.

04:41.324 --> 04:42.891
YES, YOU WERE.

04:42.934 --> 04:45.154
AND I CAN SAY THAT I'M SORRY
FOR DECEIVING YOU,

04:45.197 --> 04:46.851
AND I WILL SAY THAT
FOREVER,

04:46.895 --> 04:50.290
BUT I CAN'T SAY
THAT I'M SORRY MY DAD'S ALIVE,

04:50.333 --> 04:51.769
BECAUSE I'M NOT.

04:51.813 --> 04:54.424
IT IS SO OVERWHELMING,
AND I AM SO GRATEFUL,

04:54.468 --> 04:57.297
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO EXPLAIN IT.

04:57.340 --> 04:59.908
YOU ACTED ON AN IMPULSE
SO POIGNANT AND DEEP.

04:59.951 --> 05:04.347
I KNOW WHAT IT FEELS LIKE.
I FELT IT WITH YOU.

05:04.391 --> 05:07.524
AND I'LL NEVER BE SORRY
I DID IT, EITHER.

05:07.568 --> 05:08.743
[ GASPS LIGHTLY ]

05:15.402 --> 05:16.707
[ SIGHS ]

05:16.751 --> 05:19.101
I'LL LET YOU BREATHE
IN A MINUTE. I PROMISE.

05:19.144 --> 05:21.625
I'M GOOD.

05:21.669 --> 05:24.759
SO, WHAT'S NEXT?

05:24.802 --> 05:27.152
THE REALITY IS,
YOUR DAD'S BACK --

05:27.196 --> 05:29.198
IN SWADDLING BANDAGES,
BUT HE'S BACK.

05:29.241 --> 05:32.680
AND IF WE'RE GONNA
BE ONE BIG, HAPPY,
ALBEIT UNCONVENTIONAL...

05:32.723 --> 05:34.334
FAMILY...

05:34.377 --> 05:36.553
THEN THERE ARE A LOT OF THINGS
WE NEED TO DISCUSS.

05:36.597 --> 05:38.381
WELL, I'VE ALREADY COVERED
A LOT OF GROUND --

05:38.425 --> 05:40.035
FIRST TOUCH, LIFE,
SECOND TOUCH, DEATH,

05:40.078 --> 05:41.906
AND THAT DIGBY AND I ARE
THE ONLY OTHER ALIVE-AGAINS

05:41.950 --> 05:43.647
TO BE ALIVE
LONGER THAN A MINUTE.

05:43.691 --> 05:48.217
THEN THAT LEAVES FIGURING OUT
WHAT TO DO WITH YOUR DAD.

05:48.260 --> 05:51.002
THE ONLY WAY WE CAN DO THAT
IS TOGETHER.

05:51.046 --> 05:52.308
ARE WE TOGETHER?

05:52.352 --> 05:54.310
MM.

05:54.354 --> 05:58.227
WE'RE SO "GETHERED," ELECTRONS
COULDN'T GET BETWEEN US.

05:58.270 --> 06:00.098
YOU'RE BEAMING.

06:00.142 --> 06:03.624
[ GIGGLES ]

06:03.667 --> 06:06.017
I'M NOT THE ONLY ONE.

06:06.061 --> 06:07.671
WHAT IS THAT?

06:07.715 --> 06:12.459
Narrator: THE BODY OF
NORA McQUODDY WAS WHAT THAT WAS.

06:13.764 --> 06:15.113
MERE MOMENTS EARLIER,

06:15.157 --> 06:19.030
THE METICULOUS
PAPEN HARBOR LIGHTHOUSE KEEPER,

06:19.074 --> 06:21.293
OBSESSING
OVER A STUBBORN SMUDGE,

06:21.337 --> 06:22.773
WOULD MAKE A FATAL MISTAKE,

06:22.817 --> 06:26.603
BECAUSE WHAT NORA DIDN'T NOTICE
WAS HER KILLER...

06:30.215 --> 06:34.306
...WHO WANTED EVERYONE
TO NOTICE HER.

06:37.832 --> 06:39.529
Reporter:
...COUNTY CORONER'S OFFICE.

06:39.573 --> 06:41.226
AT THIS TIME,
THE PRIME SUSPECT,

06:41.270 --> 06:43.751
SEEN FLEEING FROM THE SCENE
IN A YELLOW FISHERMAN'S JACKET,

06:43.794 --> 06:47.319
HAS BEEN IDENTIFIED AS THE
LIGHTHOUSE KEEPER'S HUSBAND,

06:47.363 --> 06:48.538
MERLE McQUODDY.

06:48.582 --> 06:52.455
THAT'S SOME SHADY
SHADOW PUPPET.

06:52.499 --> 06:54.196
MERLE McQUODDY!

06:54.239 --> 06:57.242
OUT OF ALL THE ENIGMATIC,
ESOTERIC LOCAL GHOST STORIES,

06:57.286 --> 06:59.462
HIS IS MY ABSOLUTE FAVE.

06:59.506 --> 07:01.333
MERLE McQUODDY
WAS A SALTY SAILOR

07:01.377 --> 07:04.815
WHO LEFT HIS LIGHTHOUSE-KEEPER
WIFE AND YOUNG CHILD

07:04.859 --> 07:07.470
ON A FISHING VOYAGE
10 YEARS AGO,

07:07.514 --> 07:08.776
ONLY TO VANISH...

07:08.819 --> 07:10.386
...WITHOUT A TRACE.

07:10.430 --> 07:11.779
BOM BOM BA-BOM

07:11.822 --> 07:13.476
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:13.520 --> 07:16.740
MARINERS SWEAR HIS GHOST HAUNTS
THE SEA CAVES BY THE HARBOR.

07:16.784 --> 07:19.177
AND WHEN THE LIGHTHOUSE SHINES,

07:19.221 --> 07:21.745
YOU CAN HEAR HIS GHOULISH MOANS

07:21.789 --> 07:25.357
AS HE CRIES OUT
FOR SOMEONE -- ANYONE --

07:25.401 --> 07:26.576
TO GUIDE HIM HOME AND --

07:26.620 --> 07:27.751
-BOO!
-AAH!

07:27.795 --> 07:29.710
[ LAUGHS ]

07:29.753 --> 07:31.625
BOOED YA!

07:31.668 --> 07:34.802
Narrator: IN ACTUAL FACT,
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

07:34.845 --> 07:38.806
MERLE McQUODDY DID, INDEED,
LEAVE HIS WIFE AND CHILD

07:38.849 --> 07:42.070
ON A VOYAGE 10 YEARS AGO.

07:42.113 --> 07:46.030
HIS BOAT, THE KNOCKOUT NORA,
WAS LOADED DOWN WITH DUNGENESS,

07:46.074 --> 07:51.819
WHEN IT WAS KNOCKED OUT BY
THE CATEGORY 5 TYPHOON TYRONE.

07:51.862 --> 07:53.342
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:53.385 --> 07:55.562
Narrator: FOR 9 YEARS,
11 MONTHS, AND 5 DAYS,

07:55.605 --> 07:57.433
THE PRESUMED GHOST,
MERLE McQUODDY,

07:57.477 --> 08:02.656
WAS VERY MUCH ALIVE
AND ALONE ON A DESERTED ISLAND.

08:02.699 --> 08:04.440
ALL THE WHILE, NORA KEPT WATCH,

08:04.484 --> 08:07.704
PRAYING THAT ONE DAY
HER HUSBAND WOULD COME HOME

08:07.748 --> 08:10.707
AND LIFE WOULD RETURN
TO THE WAY IT ONCE WAS.

08:10.751 --> 08:14.929
AFTER A NEAR DECADE OF WAITING,
HER PRAYERS WERE ANSWERED

08:14.972 --> 08:19.368
WHEN MERLE WAS RESCUED
BY A GAY FAMILY CRUISE SHIP.

08:21.326 --> 08:24.547
BUT MERLE McQUODDY WAS NOT
THE MAN HE USED TO BE.

08:24.591 --> 08:26.723
HE'D ROAM THE BEACHES
AT MIDNIGHT,

08:26.767 --> 08:29.204
FLEW INTO RAGES,
SHUNNED INDOOR PLUMBING!

08:29.247 --> 08:32.555
AND NOW HE'S A MURDERER
AT LARGE, AND --

08:32.599 --> 08:34.514
-AAAAAH!
-AAAAAH! AAAAAH!

08:40.868 --> 08:42.086
MR. COD?

08:42.130 --> 08:43.784
I WAS TOLD
I COULD FIND YOU HERE.

08:43.827 --> 08:45.002
MY NAME
IS ELLIOT McQUODDY.

08:45.046 --> 08:46.351
ELLIOT McQUODDY?

08:46.395 --> 08:49.267
SON OF URBAN LEGEND
MERLE McQUODDY.

08:49.311 --> 08:52.227
PLEASE, YOU HAVE TO CLEAR
MY FATHER OF MY MOTHER'S MURDER.

08:57.624 --> 08:59.713
MY ENTIRE LIFE SAVINGS --

08:59.756 --> 09:01.018
EVERYTHING I EVER FOUND

09:01.062 --> 09:03.107
COMBING THE SHORE
WITH MY METAL DETECTOR.

09:03.151 --> 09:04.631
BY ALL MEANS,

09:04.674 --> 09:07.590
BRING ME UP TO TEMPO
ON WHAT HAPPENED TONIGHT.

09:07.634 --> 09:09.287
MOM DROPPED ME OFF
AT THE MOVIES

09:09.331 --> 09:11.159
WITH A BATCH
OF HOMEMADE PEANUT BRITTLE.

09:11.202 --> 09:15.293
AFTERWARDS, WHEN I DIDN'T SEE
THE MINIVAN, I WALKED HOME.

09:15.337 --> 09:17.252
COPS WERE EVERYWHERE.

09:17.295 --> 09:18.949
THEY TOLD ME SHE WAS DEAD.

09:18.993 --> 09:20.690
AND DAD WAS
NOWHERE TO BE FOUND.

09:20.734 --> 09:21.952
Ned: YOU WANT IT
A LA MODE?

09:21.996 --> 09:23.606
THE POWER'S OUT,

09:23.650 --> 09:26.391
AND THE ICE CREAM WON'T BE
SO MUCH ICE AS CREAM SOON.

09:26.435 --> 09:27.871
LOTS AND LOTS, PLEASE.

09:27.915 --> 09:30.221
WHO KNOWS
WHEN I'LL GET ANOTHER MEAL,

09:30.265 --> 09:31.266
WITHOUT MOM TO MAKE IT?

09:31.309 --> 09:34.312
OH, YOU POOR BOY.

09:34.356 --> 09:36.924
THERE, THERE.

09:36.967 --> 09:38.752
NOT HERE, HERE.

09:38.795 --> 09:40.318
Emerson: SORRY, KID.

09:40.362 --> 09:42.407
EYEWITNESSES SAY
THEY SAW MERLE McQUODDY

09:42.451 --> 09:43.670
RUNNING AWAY
FROM THE SCENE.

09:43.713 --> 09:45.628
ALL THEY SAW
WAS A YELLOW RAINCOAT.

09:45.672 --> 09:47.456
THERE'S NO WAY
HE'D HURT MY MOTHER.

09:47.499 --> 09:51.982
AFTER 10 YEARS OF WAITING,
OUR FAMILY WAS FINALLY REUNITED.

09:52.026 --> 09:56.334
I DON'T KNOW WHERE MY DAD IS,
AND EVEN IF I FIND HIM...

09:56.378 --> 09:58.206
THEY'LL TAKE HIM AWAY.

09:58.249 --> 10:00.251
[ Voice breaking ]
EXCUSE ME.

10:00.295 --> 10:01.601
OH.

10:01.644 --> 10:03.254
WELL, HATE TO BE A BITCH,

10:03.298 --> 10:05.430
BUT AIN'T NO WAY IN THE WORLD
I'M TAKING THIS CASE.

10:05.474 --> 10:07.824
YOU THINK MERLE McQUODDY
MURDERED NORA.

10:07.868 --> 10:10.087
MERLE McQUODDY'S SHIP RETURNED
MINUS A FEW OARS,

10:10.131 --> 10:12.699
MAKING IT A VERY EASY LEAP
FROM CAPTAIN TO KILLER.

10:12.742 --> 10:15.440
NOTHING THIS KID HAD TO SAY
MAKES ME THINK OTHERWISE.

10:15.484 --> 10:16.833
PLUS, I DON'T WORK
IN THE RAIN.

10:16.877 --> 10:19.357
CLEARLY, YOU DON'T HATE
BEING A BITCH THAT MUCH.

10:19.401 --> 10:20.837
I'LL KICK YOU BACK
MY THIRD OF THE CUT.

10:20.881 --> 10:22.839
AND IF YOU'RE DOING
MY THIRD OF THE WORK,

10:22.883 --> 10:25.189
THEN, UM, I'M GONNA TAKE
A PERSONAL DAY

10:25.233 --> 10:28.889
TO DEAL
WITH PERSONAL...

10:28.932 --> 10:32.022
...PERSONS.

10:32.066 --> 10:33.154
WELL...

10:33.197 --> 10:34.677
[ COINS JINGLE ]

10:34.721 --> 10:37.158
...LOOK LIKE PAPA'S GONNA NEED
A NEW RAINCOAT.

10:38.202 --> 10:40.988
AND LEATHER CONDITIONER.

10:41.031 --> 10:42.337
YOU SEE
THIS WATER DAMAGE?

10:42.380 --> 10:44.687
THESE WING TIPS
WERE CUSTOM-COBBLED.

10:44.731 --> 10:46.558
CAN WE HURRY? I'M SUPPOSED TO
SEE CHUCK'S FATHER.

10:46.602 --> 10:48.909
I WANT TO GET HIM A...
"WELCOME BACK TO LIFE" GIFT.

10:48.952 --> 10:52.216
OH, I GOT THE PERFECT GIFT --
TAP DAD BACK TO THE GRAVE.

10:52.260 --> 10:53.609
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

10:53.653 --> 10:55.306
BECAUSE YOU ARE IN
OVER YOUR HEAD.

10:55.350 --> 10:58.092
YOU CAN PUT A LEASH ON A DOG.
YOU KNOW WHY? 'CAUSE IT'S A DOG.

10:58.135 --> 11:00.442
BUT YOU CAN'T PUT ONE
ON A WAR VETERAN

11:00.485 --> 11:02.139
THAT WAS CUT DOWN
IN HIS PRIME.

11:02.183 --> 11:03.750
BEFORE LONG,
HE'S GONNA BREAK FREE.

11:03.793 --> 11:05.447
THEN HE'LL JUST BE
RUNNING THE STREETS,

11:05.490 --> 11:07.710
TELLING THE WORLD
WHAT YOU CAN DO.

11:07.754 --> 11:09.407
TAP THAT.

11:09.451 --> 11:12.323
UGH. THIS IS CHUCK'S CHANCE
AT HAVING A FAMILY AGAIN.

11:12.367 --> 11:13.716
I CAN'T...

11:13.760 --> 11:14.978
TAP THAT.

11:15.022 --> 11:16.850
SO MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
AN ACCIDENT.

11:16.893 --> 11:19.504
TRIP OVER AN OTTOMAN
AND DICK VAN DYKE THAT ASS.

11:19.548 --> 11:21.332
OHH.

11:21.376 --> 11:23.160
FINE.
I SAID MY PIECE.

11:23.204 --> 11:25.859
LET'S GET FACE-TO-FACE
WITH LIGHTHOUSE LADY.

11:25.902 --> 11:27.425
WHOA! WHOA!

11:27.469 --> 11:29.427
WHAT HAPPENED TO HER FACE?
SHE'S BEEN EFFACED!

11:32.213 --> 11:33.475
HMM?
MRS. McQUODDY?

11:33.518 --> 11:35.607
PRESENT CONDITIONS
ARE COLD, RAINY,

11:35.651 --> 11:37.740
WITH A 100% CHANCE
OF "YOU'RE DEAD."

11:37.784 --> 11:40.482
WE'RE HOPING THAT YOU CAN
TELL US WHO KILLED YOU.

11:40.525 --> 11:41.744
[ MUTTERS ]

11:41.788 --> 11:43.920
OH, HELL.
WE GOT A MELTY MOUTH.

11:43.964 --> 11:45.052
[ MUTTERING ]

11:45.095 --> 11:46.183
"YES" OR "NO"
QUESTIONS.

11:46.227 --> 11:47.489
SHE CAN'T NOD.
HOW CAN SHE NOD?

11:47.532 --> 11:50.535
[ TAPPING ]
WHAT IS THAT TAPPING?

11:50.579 --> 11:51.754
I DON'T THINK
SHE'S TAPPING.

11:51.798 --> 11:54.017
I THINK SHE'S TALKING --
IN MORSE CODE.

11:54.061 --> 11:55.236
[ MUTTERS ]

11:55.279 --> 11:56.846
HOW DO YOU KNOW
MORSE CODE?

11:56.890 --> 11:58.152
CHARLES CHARLES TAUGHT IT
TO CHUCK AND ME

11:58.195 --> 11:59.457
WHEN WE WERE KIDS
SO WE COULD COMMUNICATE

11:59.501 --> 12:02.373
FROM OUR BEDROOM WINDOWS
WITH FLASHLIGHTS.

12:02.417 --> 12:03.635
-MRS. McQUODDY?
-MM-HMM?

12:03.679 --> 12:05.768
WHO COMMITTED
YOUR MURDER?

12:05.812 --> 12:10.207
P...C...H...S.

12:10.251 --> 12:11.469
IS THAT ALL?

12:11.513 --> 12:13.428
[ MUTTERING LOUDLY ]

12:13.471 --> 12:14.516
TIME'S UP.

12:14.559 --> 12:15.560
[ MUTTERING STOPS ]

12:15.604 --> 12:17.954
P-C-H-S.

12:17.998 --> 12:21.001
"PIC-HISS."

12:21.044 --> 12:23.220
PIC-HISS!

12:23.264 --> 12:25.875
PEACHES!

12:25.919 --> 12:27.616
IT'S AN ACRONYM, FOOL.

12:27.659 --> 12:29.749
"PAPEN COUNTY
HISTORICAL SOCIETY."

12:29.792 --> 12:33.840
AN OLD LIGHTHOUSE LIKE NORA'S
IS BOUND TO HAVE INTEREST.

12:33.883 --> 12:35.232
"PEACHES."

12:37.321 --> 12:39.628
OLIVE?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

12:39.671 --> 12:42.109
LOOKING AND FINDING YOU TWO,
WHICH IS A CINCH, NATCH,

12:42.152 --> 12:45.112
'CAUSE I'M SUCH AN ACE
JUNIOR P.I. IN TRAINING.

12:45.155 --> 12:48.506
LOOK WHAT MAMA GOT PAPA.

12:48.550 --> 12:51.205
HA! I BOUGHT ONE
FOR YOU, TOO, NED.

12:51.248 --> 12:52.423
[ LAUGHS ]

12:52.467 --> 12:53.990
AND ONE FOR ME, TOO,
OF COURSE.

12:54.034 --> 12:56.863
'CAUSE TOGETHER,
WE'RE A CRIME-FIGHTING TEAM.

12:56.906 --> 12:58.473
WHAT DO YOU SAY, PAPA?

12:58.516 --> 13:02.172
UH, I THINK YOU AND PAPA
ARE GONNA HAVE A GRAND OLD TIME

13:02.216 --> 13:05.132
WHILE I, UH...
TAKE CARE OF A...THING.

13:08.570 --> 13:09.876
BUT --

13:09.919 --> 13:12.443
HEY! MOOD-SWING SALLY,
ANCHORS AWEIGH!

13:16.143 --> 13:17.448
DADDY, YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT SOME PIE?

13:17.492 --> 13:19.668
THANKS, BUTTON,
BUT I'LL HAVE CAKE.

13:19.711 --> 13:23.803
SINCE WHEN DO YOU EAT PIE?
YOU HATE PIE.

13:23.846 --> 13:27.023
WELL, THIS IS THE ONE
THAT WON ME OVER.

13:27.067 --> 13:29.504
SO, NO CAKE?
AT ALL?

13:29.547 --> 13:31.201
OH, WELL.

13:31.245 --> 13:33.682
WELL, LET'S NOT
WORRY ABOUT PIE.

13:33.725 --> 13:37.860
UH, THIS FAMILY HAS
BIGGER THINGS TO DISCUSS.

13:37.904 --> 13:40.863
TO THAT END...

13:40.907 --> 13:43.300
"MOVE MR. CHARLES
FROM NED'S CHILDHOOD HOME

13:43.344 --> 13:44.519
TO NED'S APARTMENT."

13:44.562 --> 13:46.390
YOU KILLED A TREE FOR THIS?

13:46.434 --> 13:48.479
I'M HAPPY AS A CLAM
RIGHT HERE.

13:48.523 --> 13:50.177
THE PROBLEM IS, LILY AND VIVIAN
ARE RIGHT HERE, TOO,

13:50.220 --> 13:52.309
AND FOR A COUPLE OF AGORAPHOBES,
THEY GET AROUND.

13:52.353 --> 13:54.572
WE CAN'T RISK THEM COMING BACK
AND DISCOVERING YOU,

13:54.616 --> 13:56.531
THEREBY DISCOVERING THE TRUTH
ABOUT ALL OF US.

13:56.574 --> 13:58.925
FROM THERE,
IT'S A HOP, SKIP, AND A JUMP

13:58.968 --> 14:02.145
TO ANGRY MOBS
WITH PITCHFORKS AND TORCHES.

14:02.189 --> 14:03.755
IF I BUNK WITH YOU,

14:03.799 --> 14:05.757
YOU'D KILL ME AGAIN
JUST BY PASSING THE PEPPER.

14:05.801 --> 14:07.890
THERE ARE MANY SAFEGUARDS
ALREADY IN PLACE.

14:07.934 --> 14:09.370
TRUTH BE TOLD,
YOU TOUCHING ME DEAD

14:09.413 --> 14:10.937
DOESN'T SCARE ME
NEARLY AS MUCH

14:10.980 --> 14:12.939
AS THE THOUGHT OF YOU
DOING THAT TO MY DAUGHTER.

14:12.982 --> 14:15.767
SIR, I COULD NEVER
HURT CHUCK.

14:15.811 --> 14:17.378
OH, SURE YOU COULD,
DEADLY NEDLY.

14:17.421 --> 14:19.032
YOU COULD FORGET
SHE'S WALKING BEHIND YOU

14:19.075 --> 14:21.861
AND STOP TO TIE YOUR SHOE OR
TRIP OVER A FORGOTTEN NEWSPAPER.

14:21.904 --> 14:23.645
NO NUMBER OF REDUNDANT
PRECAUTIONS CAN ASSURE

14:23.688 --> 14:26.387
THAT YOU WON'T INADVERTENTLY
KILL HER FOR GOOD AND FOREVER,

14:26.430 --> 14:28.215
UNLESS YOU'RE NOT
IN THE SAME VICINITY,

14:28.258 --> 14:30.913
WHICH IS WHY
WE'RE GONNA MAKE A DEAL.

14:30.957 --> 14:32.959
I GO QUIETLY
AND PLAY BY YOUR RULES...

14:33.002 --> 14:34.874
[ GASPS ]

14:34.917 --> 14:37.224
...AND YOU NEVER SEE
CHARLOTTE AGAIN.

14:42.664 --> 14:45.449
THE FIRST FAMILY
OF PAPEN COUNTY.

14:45.493 --> 14:48.017
BUNCH OF BLOND-OVER-BLUE
CHILDREN OF THE CORN.

14:48.061 --> 14:50.585
WHICH ONE
WE GONNA GRILL FIRST?

14:50.628 --> 14:53.501
GUS -- THE ROSEMARY KENNEDY
OF THE CLAN.

14:53.544 --> 14:55.024
WHILE BROTHERS
ONE THROUGH FOUR

14:55.068 --> 14:57.766
RUN THE FAMILY'S
COMMERCIAL-REAL-ESTATE EMPIRE

14:57.809 --> 14:59.246
AND SOUTH ASIAN
CALL CENTERS,

14:59.289 --> 15:02.553
ALL HE GOT WAS
THE HISTORICAL SOCIETY.

15:02.597 --> 15:06.166
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

15:06.209 --> 15:07.254
[ BOTH SIGH ]

15:07.297 --> 15:08.385
Gus: OLIVE SNOOK?

15:08.429 --> 15:12.302
MR. PAPEN.
WELCOME TO THE PIE HOLE.

15:12.346 --> 15:14.304
UH, DID YOU GET
MY APPLICATION

15:14.348 --> 15:16.393
TO DECLARE
OUR WONDERFUL ESTABLISHMENT

15:16.437 --> 15:17.568
A HISTORICAL MONUMENT?

15:17.612 --> 15:19.092
THAT APPLICATION WAS DENIED

15:19.135 --> 15:20.920
THE MOMENT YOU PEOPLE DESTROYED
AN EXEMPLARY SPECIMEN

15:20.963 --> 15:23.183
OF TURN-OF-THE-CENTURY
BEAUX ARTS ARCHITECTURE

15:23.226 --> 15:26.142
WITH THE ADDITION
OF A STUCCO-CRUST OVERHANG.

15:26.186 --> 15:27.491
Told you.

15:27.535 --> 15:29.189
WELL, UH,
SINCE YOU'RE ALREADY HERE,

15:29.232 --> 15:31.495
YOU MIND ANSWERING A FEW
QUESTIONS ABOUT NORA McQUODDY?

15:31.539 --> 15:33.671
HAVE THEY FOUND
THE BLOODTHIRSTY HUSBAND?

15:33.715 --> 15:35.499
MERLE? NO.

15:35.543 --> 15:38.633
WHAT IS NORA'S CONNECTION
TO THE P.C.H.S.?

15:38.676 --> 15:40.069
WITH HER HUSBAND
LOST AT SEA,

15:40.113 --> 15:42.463
NORA COULDN'T AFFORD
THE LIGHTHOUSE UPKEEP.

15:42.506 --> 15:43.986
I USED
MY FAMILY INFLUENCE

15:44.030 --> 15:46.554
TO DECLARE IT
A PROTECTED HISTORIC MONUMENT.

15:46.597 --> 15:48.382
I APPOINTED NORA
THE LIGHTHOUSE STEWARD

15:48.425 --> 15:50.471
AND THE McQUODDYS ITS GUARDIAN
UNTIL THE FAMILY LINE DIES OUT

15:50.514 --> 15:52.429
OR THE SUN SWALLOWS THE EARTH
IN A SOLAR FLARE,

15:52.473 --> 15:54.040
KILLING US ALL.

15:54.083 --> 15:57.391
WELL, THAT MEANS ELLIOT'S
IN CHARGE OF THE LIGHTHOUSE NOW.

15:57.434 --> 15:59.959
OTHER THAN THAT,
I DIDN'T REALLY KNOW NORA.

16:00.002 --> 16:03.353
IF YOU WANT TO LEARN MORE,
TALK TO ANNABELLE VANDERSLOOP.

16:03.397 --> 16:05.660
THEY VOLUNTEERED TOGETHER
IN THE DIORAMA EXHIBIT.

16:05.703 --> 16:10.447
SUCH A DEPRESSING WORD,
"DIORAMA."

16:10.491 --> 16:13.581
IT HAS "DIE" IN IT.

16:13.624 --> 16:16.366
I LIKE "RAMA."

16:16.410 --> 16:18.978
OKAY, SO,THIS...

16:19.021 --> 16:22.285
IS SO WE CAN KEEP IN CONSTANT
CONTACT IN THE PRESENT,

16:22.329 --> 16:26.898
AND THIS IS
SO YOU CAN REGAIN CONTACT

16:26.942 --> 16:28.683
WITH YOUR PAST.

16:33.035 --> 16:34.210
WELL, I'LL BE.

16:34.254 --> 16:35.255
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:35.298 --> 16:37.039
THANK YOU, BUTTON.

16:37.083 --> 16:38.040
[ THUD ]

16:38.084 --> 16:39.520
UM...RIGHT.

16:39.563 --> 16:42.001
WELL, UH...
I'LL LEAVE YOU TO SETTLE IN.

16:45.526 --> 16:47.136
DIGBY, COME ON.

16:59.322 --> 17:01.237
[ SIGHS ]

17:03.761 --> 17:05.154
THERE'S MILK
TO GO WITH THE CAKE.

17:05.198 --> 17:06.938
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO GO
TO ALL THAT TROUBLE.

17:06.982 --> 17:10.551
I WANTED TO.
IT'S A HUGE ADJUSTMENT.

17:10.594 --> 17:12.118
THAT'S BIG OF YOU, KID.

17:12.161 --> 17:13.902
WE WON'T GET ANYWHERE
WITHOUT A LITTLE TEAMWORK.

17:13.945 --> 17:18.211
THAT'S A PERFECT SEGUE
TO OUR PLAYBOOK.

17:18.254 --> 17:21.431
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

17:21.475 --> 17:22.911
UH, THIS IS EVERYTHING

17:22.954 --> 17:24.347
THAT PERTAINS
TO THE ALIVE-AGAIN LIFESTYLE

17:24.391 --> 17:25.653
WITH YOUR PARTICULAR
ALIVE-AGAIN SITUATION.

17:25.696 --> 17:27.481
YOU MEAN MY CORPSE FACE?

17:27.524 --> 17:29.309
CORPSE FACE...

17:29.352 --> 17:31.006
TAKEN INTO CONSIDERATION.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.747
IN SHORT, STAY INSIDE

17:32.790 --> 17:35.619
WITH THE DOORS LOCKED
AND THE CURTAINS DRAWN.

17:35.663 --> 17:37.012
FOOD DELIVERIES
ARE VERBOTEN.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.840
HOWEVER, TELEPHONE USE
IS UNRESTRICTED,

17:38.883 --> 17:41.016
AS LONG AS YOU CHOOSE
FROM THE LIST OF CLEARED
ALIASES ON PAGE 13

17:41.060 --> 17:42.670
WHEN COMMUNICATING
WITH THE OUTSIDE WORLD.

17:42.713 --> 17:46.761
FOR THE FIRST MONTH, I WOULD
RECOMMEND WEARING LATEX GLOVES.

17:46.804 --> 17:48.328
I ALREADY GOT GLOVES ON.

17:48.371 --> 17:50.721
NO HARM
IN DOUBLE-BAGGING IT, EH?

17:50.765 --> 17:53.811
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:53.855 --> 17:55.726
SIR,
I'M REALLY TRYING HERE.

17:55.770 --> 17:57.902
INSTEAD OF
BUTTERING ME UP...

17:57.946 --> 18:01.297
WHY DON'T WE DEAL
WITH THE ELEPHANT IN THE ROOM?

18:01.341 --> 18:02.907
YOU KILLED ME.

18:02.951 --> 18:05.649
I KNEW YOUR PARENTS, NED.
YOU WERE RAISED RIGHT.

18:05.693 --> 18:06.824
HOW ABOUT AN APOLOGY?

18:06.868 --> 18:08.435
I'M SORRY.

18:08.478 --> 18:10.524
"ALL IS FORGIVEN" IS GONNA BE
A LONG TIME COMING.

18:10.567 --> 18:12.613
YOU NEED
TO RESPECT THAT.

18:12.656 --> 18:14.223
ALRIGHT?

18:14.267 --> 18:17.531
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I GOT A BUNCH OF READING TO DO.

18:19.881 --> 18:22.144
Narrator: WHILE CHARLES CHARLES
WAS READING,

18:22.188 --> 18:24.059
OLIVE SNOOK
AND THE PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR

18:24.103 --> 18:27.758
WERE LISTENING
TO ONE ANNABELLE VANDERSLOOP.

18:27.802 --> 18:29.369
NORA AND I
WERE BEST FRIENDS.

18:29.412 --> 18:32.502
WE MET THROUGH THE NOTABLE
WIDOWS OF PAPEN COUNTY.

18:32.546 --> 18:35.723
WE PAID TRIBUTE TO OUR NOTABLE
HUSBANDS' NOTABLE DEATHS

18:35.766 --> 18:38.813
THROUGH THE MINIATURE MEDIUM
OF DIORAMA.

18:38.856 --> 18:40.684
Olive:
I LOVE DIORAMAS.

18:40.728 --> 18:41.772
HOW CAN I GET INVOLVED?

18:41.816 --> 18:43.034
ARE YOU A WIDOW?

18:43.078 --> 18:44.253
-NO.
-OH.

18:44.297 --> 18:45.472
UNFORTUNATELY,
I'M SINGLE.

18:45.515 --> 18:47.126
OHH.

18:47.169 --> 18:49.345
BUT I DO HAVE A BELOVED HORSE
WHO BOUGHT THE FARM.

18:49.389 --> 18:50.607
I COULD DIORAM THAT.

18:50.651 --> 18:52.392
SORRY.
EXPIRED SPOUSES ONLY.

18:52.435 --> 18:53.610
MM.

18:53.654 --> 18:56.526
FOR EXAMPLE,
MY LATE HUSBAND,

18:56.570 --> 18:59.181
MUNITIONS MANUFACTURER
ADOLPH VANDERSLOOP,

18:59.225 --> 19:00.878
WENT OUT WITH A BANG.

19:00.922 --> 19:05.187
AN ERRANT 4th OF JULY ROCKET
FLEW INTO AN OPEN WINDOW

19:05.231 --> 19:07.668
WHILE HE WAS
TAKING INVENTORY.

19:07.711 --> 19:08.886
OH.

19:08.930 --> 19:10.758
[ WHISTLING, POPPING ]

19:10.801 --> 19:12.455
OH! [ LAUGHS ]

19:12.499 --> 19:18.026
ONE CAN NEVER ADD ENOUGH GLITTER
TO A HUSBAND'S MEMORY.

19:18.069 --> 19:20.246
MISS SNOOK, DO YOU SEE
HOW YOUR PONY DEATH

19:20.289 --> 19:23.205
MIGHT MAKE A MOCKERY
OF OUR LEGITIMATE EFFORTS?

19:23.249 --> 19:26.948
DO YOU SEE HOW YOU HAVE
COTTON BALLS STUCK TO YOUR ASS?

19:26.991 --> 19:28.689
OH! I WAS LOOKING
FOR THOSE!

19:28.732 --> 19:31.692
YEAH, WELL, I'M LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING -- INFORMATION...

19:31.735 --> 19:33.259
ON WHETHER
NORA McQUODDY'S HUSBAND

19:33.302 --> 19:35.261
MADE HIMSELF
A NOTABLE WIDOWER.

19:35.304 --> 19:37.132
I WAS WITH SWEET NORA
WHEN SHE HEARD THE NEWS

19:37.176 --> 19:39.700
THAT HOMOSEXUAL BOAT
HAD RESCUED MERLE.

19:39.743 --> 19:42.398
CAN YOU IMAGINE THE JOY
OF STARTING OVER

19:42.442 --> 19:45.880
WITH A HUSBAND
YOU THOUGHT YOU'D LOST?

19:45.923 --> 19:47.316
NO. YOU CAN'T.

19:47.360 --> 19:50.014
WELL, ANYWAY,
NORA WAS THE FIRST TO ADMIT

19:50.058 --> 19:51.799
THAT SHE WAS
AN OVERPROTECTIVE MOTHER,

19:51.842 --> 19:53.104
BUT WITH MERLE HOME

19:53.148 --> 19:55.455
AND ELLIOT SO DESPERATE
TO BOND WITH HIM,

19:55.498 --> 19:57.674
IT QUICKLY BECAME
TWO AGAINST ONE.

19:57.718 --> 19:59.241
SHE JUST FINALLY
HAD TO PUT HER FOOT DOWN.

19:59.285 --> 20:00.547
ON WHAT?

20:00.590 --> 20:01.852
OH, CRAZY THINGS,
LIKE, YOU KNOW,

20:01.896 --> 20:04.855
FATHER/SON SAILING TRIPS
AROUND THE WORLD.

20:04.899 --> 20:06.944
SHE ABSOLUTELY
FORBADE IT.

20:06.988 --> 20:08.946
AND I GUESS
THAT WAS THE FINAL STRAW

20:08.990 --> 20:12.776
BEFORE MERLE SNAPPED,
KILLED HER, AND WENT AWOL.

20:12.820 --> 20:14.865
OH, SOMETIMES
I JUST THINK TO MYSELF,

20:14.909 --> 20:18.565
"LIFE -- YOU CAN'T
MAKE THIS CRAP UP."

20:18.608 --> 20:20.219
YEAH, WELL, UM,
THANKS FOR YOUR TIME.

20:20.262 --> 20:22.133
-THANK YOU.
-THANK YOU.

20:22.177 --> 20:24.527
OH! [ CHUCKLES ]

20:24.571 --> 20:28.270
WELL, GOOD LUCK.

20:28.314 --> 20:31.186
SPEAKING OF CRAP,
ELLIOT SEEMS TO BE FULL OF IT.

20:31.230 --> 20:32.709
WE MET
A HEARTBROKEN MAMA'S BOY

20:32.753 --> 20:34.363
WHO NEVER MENTIONED
FEUDS WITH MAMA.

20:34.407 --> 20:35.756
WHAT GIVES?

20:35.799 --> 20:37.714
THAT'S JUST
WHAT WE'RE GONNA ASK HIM.

20:42.153 --> 20:46.027
DON'T BOTHER SIGNING IN.
THE OPEN HOUSE IS OFF.

20:46.070 --> 20:47.289
WHO ARE YOU?

20:47.333 --> 20:49.378
WILLIE GHERKIN --
SMILEY REALTY.

20:49.422 --> 20:51.337
AW. YOU LOST YOUR SMILE,
PICKLE.

20:51.380 --> 20:53.687
I THOUGHT
IT WAS TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE.

20:53.730 --> 20:55.558
THIS LIGHTHOUSE
LANDS IN MY LAP,

20:55.602 --> 20:57.647
AND NOW I FIND OUT
I CAN'T SELL IT

20:57.691 --> 21:00.607
BECAUSE IT'S A PROTECTED
HISTORICAL MONUMENT!

21:00.650 --> 21:04.611
THIS IS SO NOT THE WAY
THE SECRET IS SUPPOSED TO WORK.

21:04.654 --> 21:06.003
WHERE'S THE OWNER?

21:06.047 --> 21:08.005
ELLIOT?
THAT LITTLE BOWL-CUT SPLIT.

21:08.049 --> 21:10.921
BUT NOT BEFORE I ADVANCED HIM
10 GRAND AGAINST THE SALE.

21:10.965 --> 21:13.489
SAID HE AND HIS FATHER
WERE GOING OUT OF TOWN

21:13.533 --> 21:14.621
AND NEEDED CASH QUICK.

21:14.664 --> 21:16.057
IS THAT LEGAL?

21:16.100 --> 21:18.668
HOW SHOULD I KNOW?
I JUST GOT MY LICENSE.

21:18.712 --> 21:19.974
AH, SCREW IT.

21:20.017 --> 21:22.498
I'M GOING BACK
TO PERSONAL TRAINING --

21:22.542 --> 21:23.804
WHERE THERE'S RESPECT.

21:23.847 --> 21:26.676
EXCUSE ME.

21:26.720 --> 21:28.112
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:28.156 --> 21:29.766
HEY,
TRY THIS ON FOR SIZE.

21:29.810 --> 21:31.377
SO, MERLE KILLS NORA,

21:31.420 --> 21:37.861
AND THEN ELLIOT HIRES ME
TO TAKE THE SUSPICION OFF MERLE.

21:37.905 --> 21:39.907
AND THEN ELLIOT GOES
AND GETS THE FUNDS

21:39.950 --> 21:43.345
SO THEY CAN TAKE THEIR
LITTLE FATHER-AND-SON TRIP.

21:43.389 --> 21:45.216
BUT IF THEY DID
SCORE A SLOOP,

21:45.260 --> 21:47.523
THERE'S NO WAY THEY'RE
TAKING IT OUT IN THIS WEATHER.

21:47.567 --> 21:48.655
THEY MUST BE HIDING.

21:48.698 --> 21:49.699
Let's smoke 'em out.

21:49.743 --> 21:51.484
EH.

21:51.527 --> 21:54.400
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU GOT ME
WORKING IN THIS DOWNPOUR.

21:54.443 --> 21:56.445
YEAH, WHAT'S UP WITH THAT,
ANYWAY, RAIN-HATER?

21:56.489 --> 22:00.406
I MEAN, I'D GET IT
IF YOU WERE A CAT OR HAD HAIR.

22:00.449 --> 22:01.798
OR GOT DUMPED.

22:06.237 --> 22:08.718
BACK IN THE RAINY DAY,
MY EX AND I USED TO HOLE UP

22:08.762 --> 22:10.981
WITH A BOTTLE OF BRANDY
AND SOME TOMATO SOUP,

22:11.025 --> 22:13.897
AND WE WOULDN'T COME OUT
UNTIL THE SUN DID.

22:13.941 --> 22:15.682
[ SIGHS ]

22:15.725 --> 22:17.118
NOW...

22:17.161 --> 22:18.772
WHENEVER THE DROPS FALL,

22:18.815 --> 22:22.166
IT REMINDS ME OF EVERYTHING
I LOST AND AIN'T GONNA GET BACK.

22:22.210 --> 22:23.472
HAPPY?

22:23.516 --> 22:25.039
LET'S WAIT IT OUT HERE
A BIT.

22:25.082 --> 22:27.607
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED
TO SEE THIS PLACE.

22:27.650 --> 22:30.087
BUT YOU CAN'T GET
MUCH OF A FEEL FOR IT

22:30.131 --> 22:32.612
WHEN YOU'RE TRYING
TO PEEK INSIDE.

22:32.655 --> 22:34.265
[ BOTTLE HUMS ]
AAH!

22:34.309 --> 22:36.920
ARE YOU TRYING TO GIVE ME
THE HEEBIE-JEEBIES OR SOMETHING?

22:36.964 --> 22:38.531
OR A THEORY

22:38.574 --> 22:40.881
AS TO WHERE THE MURDEROUS
McQUODDYS ARE HOLED UP.

22:40.924 --> 22:42.317
REMEMBER THE SEA CAVES

22:42.361 --> 22:44.754
MERLE'S GHOST SUPPOSEDLY HAUNTED
WITH HIS HOWLS?

22:44.798 --> 22:46.713
THERE'S NOTHING HAUNTED
ABOUT THEM.

22:46.756 --> 22:49.716
THE SOUND IS CREATED
WHEN THE WIND RUSHES
IN OFF THE WATER,

22:49.759 --> 22:50.847
KIND OF LIKE...

22:50.891 --> 22:52.458
[ BOTTLE HUMS ]

22:52.501 --> 22:54.721
ELLIOT KNOWS THOSE CAVES
LIKE THE BACK OF HIS HAND!

22:54.764 --> 22:58.028
IF HE'S IN THERE,
HE'S GONNA GET THE BACK OF MINE.

22:58.072 --> 22:59.987
[ LAUGHS ] BOO-YAH!
LET'S GO.

23:02.772 --> 23:05.558
ALRIGHT, SUGARS HAVE
BEEN RE-SUGARED, CREAMERS
HAVE BEEN RE-CREAMED.

23:05.601 --> 23:09.170
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
YOU WANT ME TO DO BEFORE
I HEAD TO THE STORE?

23:09.213 --> 23:11.041
DAD GAVE ME A LIST.

23:11.085 --> 23:12.434
UM, SLIPPERS, MOUTHWASH,

23:12.478 --> 23:16.264
AND "THE LAST 20 YEARS
OF MY LIFE BACK."

23:16.307 --> 23:18.005
-HE'S...SO FUNNY.
-HILARIOUS.

23:18.048 --> 23:19.267
IT'S BAD ENOUGH
WE CAN'T TOUCH.

23:19.310 --> 23:20.355
NOW I'M NOT ALLOWED
TO SEE YOU?

23:20.399 --> 23:22.009
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

23:22.052 --> 23:24.011
WE DON'T HAVE TO STOP
SEEING EACH OTHER.

23:24.054 --> 23:25.360
IT'S JUST
WHEN DAD'S AROUND...

23:25.404 --> 23:26.492
WHICH IS LIMITED
TO YOUR APARTMENT.

23:26.535 --> 23:28.189
HE CAN'T GO
ANYWHERE ELSE.

23:28.232 --> 23:31.279
I'M NOT EMBARRASSED TO SAY THAT
I'M SCARED OF YOUR FATHER --

23:31.322 --> 23:33.586
PETRIFIED, ACTUALLY --
AND --

23:33.629 --> 23:34.630
STOP SMILING.

23:34.674 --> 23:36.327
I CAN'T HELP IT.

23:36.371 --> 23:38.373
SOMETHING'S HAPPENING
I NEVER THOUGHT WOULD HAPPEN.

23:38.417 --> 23:40.114
MY DAD'S TORTURING
MY FIRST BOYFRIEND.

23:40.157 --> 23:42.203
-YAY.
-EXACTLY.

23:42.246 --> 23:44.727
WE GET TO BE THE TEENAGERS
WE NEVER THOUGHT WE'D GET TO BE.

23:44.771 --> 23:47.208
YOU BECAUSE YOU WERE LOCKED UP
IN SOME BOARDING SCHOOL

23:47.251 --> 23:49.297
AND ME BECAUSE I WAS SHUT UP
WITH MY SHUT-IN AUNTS.

23:49.340 --> 23:52.126
AND NOW YOU GET TO BE
THE STUDLY VARSITY QUARTERBACK,

23:52.169 --> 23:54.520
AND I GET TO BE
THE FLIRTY HEAD CHEERLEADER.

23:54.563 --> 23:55.782
-HMM.
-MM.

23:55.825 --> 23:59.307
WHICH MEANS
WE CAN BREAK CURFEWS

23:59.350 --> 24:01.440
AND MISLEAD OUR PARENTS

24:01.483 --> 24:04.268
AND...GENERALLY...

24:04.312 --> 24:06.227
sneak around.

24:16.193 --> 24:17.760
I MAY NEED
SOME MORE CONVINCING.

24:17.804 --> 24:19.545
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:23.462 --> 24:26.029
I'LL MEET YOU LATER
BEHIND THE BLEACHERS.

24:26.073 --> 24:28.423
BRING YOUR POM-POMS.

24:30.860 --> 24:32.471
[ SIGHS ]

24:39.216 --> 24:40.522
HELLO, NEDLY.

24:46.485 --> 24:48.138
LOOKED TO ME LIKE YOU WERE
NECKING WITH MY DAUGHTER --

24:48.182 --> 24:50.010
THE DAUGHTER YOU PROMISED
TO KEEP A DISTANCE FROM.

24:50.053 --> 24:51.838
YOU CAN'T BE HERE.
PLEASE GO BACK UPSTAIRS.

24:51.881 --> 24:54.188
OH, I'M NOT GOING
ANYWHERE.

24:54.231 --> 24:55.494
EVERYBODY OUT!

24:55.537 --> 24:57.147
WE HAVE A GAS LEAK
CAUSED BY, UH...

24:57.191 --> 25:00.629
A RADON EMISSION
CHOCK FULL OF ASBESTOS!

25:00.673 --> 25:02.065
UH, SAFETY FIRST!

25:02.109 --> 25:03.153
COVER YOUR EYES!

25:03.197 --> 25:04.503
EVERYBODY OUT!

25:12.859 --> 25:14.121
[ DOOR OPENS ]

25:14.164 --> 25:16.166
SERIOUSLY --
NO CAKE AT ALL?

25:16.210 --> 25:18.342
-I MADE YOU A CAKE.
-I'M NOT ONE FOR CHOCOLATE.

25:18.386 --> 25:21.476
WHO'S NOT FOR CHOCOLATE?!
EVERYONE AT LEAST TOLERATES IT!

25:21.520 --> 25:23.652
MR. CHARLES, YOU CAN'T BE
IN PUBLIC LIKE THIS.

25:23.696 --> 25:24.871
IF SOMEONE SEES YOU...

25:24.914 --> 25:26.612
I'LL SAY
I'M A BURN VICTIM...

25:26.655 --> 25:28.265
IF I NEED TO SAY
ANYTHING AT ALL.

25:28.309 --> 25:30.180
I'VE BEEN WALKING AROUND
FOR AN HOUR,

25:30.224 --> 25:31.747
AND NO ONE'S
LOOKED AT ME TWICE.

25:31.791 --> 25:33.096
I WONDER
IF I CAN GET MYSELF

25:33.140 --> 25:35.185
ONE OF THOSE
"HANDICAPPED PARKING" PLACARDS.

25:35.229 --> 25:37.405
THERE'S NO DRIVING!
THAT'S RULE NUMBER 17!

25:37.448 --> 25:40.800
WHY AM I SUPPOSED
TO PLAY BY THE RULES
WHEN YOU DON'T, ROMEO?

25:40.843 --> 25:43.367
I -- I'M JUST TRYING
TO KEEP YOU SAFE.

25:43.411 --> 25:45.500
LOOK, KIDDO, YOU MAY BE ABLE
TO SCARE CHARLOTTE

25:45.544 --> 25:47.328
WITH STORIES OF MOBS
AND PITCHFORKS AND TORCHES,

25:47.371 --> 25:48.895
BUT I KNOW THE TRUTH.

25:48.938 --> 25:50.592
IF THE VILLAGERS SHOW,
THEY AREN'T COMING FOR ME.

25:50.636 --> 25:54.814
NO, THEY'RE COMING FOR THE GUY
WITH THE MAGIC FINGER.

25:54.857 --> 25:56.250
HATE TO BREAK IT
TO YOU, CHARLES,

25:56.293 --> 25:57.991
BUT NO ONE CARED
ABOUT DR. FRANKENSTEIN.

25:58.034 --> 25:59.383
THEY WERE
AFTER HIS MONSTER.

25:59.427 --> 26:01.472
AND REGARDLESS
OF WHAT YOU THINK,

26:01.516 --> 26:03.213
MY PRIORITY IS
YOUR DAUGHTER'S WELL-BEING.

26:03.257 --> 26:05.476
IF YOU WALK OUT THAT DOOR,
YOU PUT HER LIFE IN JEOPARDY.

26:05.520 --> 26:08.088
AS HER FATHER,
I'LL BE THE JUDGE OF THAT.

26:08.131 --> 26:10.612
YOU'RE NOT LEAVING.

26:10.656 --> 26:11.874
-WHOA!
-AAH!

26:11.918 --> 26:13.833
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

26:31.938 --> 26:33.940
NOT BAD
FOR A DEAD GUY, HUH?

26:33.983 --> 26:35.898
DON'T...TOUCH...ME.

26:45.081 --> 26:48.476
Narrator: AS THE TIDE TURNED
FOR THE PIE MAKER,

26:48.519 --> 26:51.740
A TURN OF THE TIDE ALLOWED
EMERSON COD AND OLIVE SNOOK

26:51.784 --> 26:55.396
TO TURN THEIR INVESTIGATION
TOWARD A SEA CAVE.

26:55.439 --> 26:57.920
IF THE McQUODDYS
ARE BARNACLED UP IN HERE,

26:57.964 --> 26:59.226
WE'LL HAVE THEM CORNERED.

26:59.269 --> 27:00.793
IF McQUODDY IS HERE,
I'LL JUST DIE!

27:00.836 --> 27:03.665
NOT BECAUSE HE'S A KILLER,
BUT BECAUSE HE'S A --

27:03.709 --> 27:04.753
AAH!

27:04.797 --> 27:06.146
AAH!

27:06.189 --> 27:08.409
EASY THERE, FRIEND!

27:08.452 --> 27:09.628
NOT FOE.

27:09.671 --> 27:11.107
YEAH, WELL,
WE FOE, FO' SHO'.

27:11.151 --> 27:14.676
EMERSON COD, P.I.,
HERE TO TRAWL YOUR ASS DOWNTOWN.

27:14.720 --> 27:15.677
WHERE'S ELLIOT?

27:15.721 --> 27:17.679
GATHERING SUPPLIES.

27:17.723 --> 27:21.161
WE KNOW ALL ABOUT THE McQUODDY
FAMILY KILLERS CRUISE.

27:21.204 --> 27:22.292
YOU TWO MURDERED NORA!

27:22.336 --> 27:24.686
YOU'RE MISTAKEN, MATEY!

27:24.730 --> 27:26.819
WHEN SHE DIED, I WAS HERE.

27:26.862 --> 27:28.951
WHY ARE YOU BUNKED UP
AL GROTTO?

27:28.995 --> 27:31.954
FOR THE PAST MONTH,
NORA AND I HAD BEEN TRYING

27:31.998 --> 27:34.957
TO PUT OUR MARRIAGE
BACK ON ITS OLD COURSE,

27:35.001 --> 27:39.396
BUT 10 YEARS APART
LEAVES YOU DIFFERENT PEOPLE.

27:39.440 --> 27:43.574
THE OTHER NIGHT,
WHILE ELLIOT WAS AT THE MOVIES,

27:43.618 --> 27:45.141
NORA CONFESSED TO ME

27:45.185 --> 27:49.189
THAT SHE'D FOUND HER BEARINGS
WITH ANOTHER MAN.

27:49.232 --> 27:53.367
BEWILDERED,
I SOUGHT SHELTER HERE.

27:53.410 --> 27:55.412
WHY NOT JUST CLEAR THINGS UP
WITH THE AUTHORITIES?

27:55.456 --> 27:57.632
[ Echoing ]
BECAUSE I'M A GHOST

27:57.676 --> 28:01.984
WITH AN ALIBI
AS THIN AS FISHING LINE!

28:02.028 --> 28:05.379
[ Normal voice ]
IT WAS ELLIOT'S IDEA
TO SET SAIL FROM HERE.

28:05.422 --> 28:09.078
SAID HE'D GARNER THE FUNDS,
AND I WOULD PREP THE VESSEL.

28:09.122 --> 28:10.732
JUST ONE HOLE
IN YOUR STORY.

28:10.776 --> 28:13.604
ELLIOT NEVER MENTIONED
NORA'S NEW SQUEEZE.

28:13.648 --> 28:15.128
NORA NEVER TOLD HIM.

28:15.171 --> 28:16.782
YEAH, WELL,
YOU BETTER COUGH UP A NAME,

28:16.825 --> 28:18.435
OR WE'RE HAULING
YOUR BUOY IN.

28:18.479 --> 28:20.002
SHE DIDN'T TELL ME
HIS NAME.

28:20.046 --> 28:22.918
BUT I FOUND THIS...

28:22.962 --> 28:24.615
IN HER PERSONAL EFFECTS.

28:24.659 --> 28:26.139
AH.
A DUTCH LOVE SPOON.

28:26.182 --> 28:28.576
MEN USED TO GIVE IT
TO THEIR WOMEN AS A SYMBOL

28:28.619 --> 28:31.448
OF THE SWEETNESS THAT
THEY'D FEED EACH OTHER FOREVER.

28:31.492 --> 28:33.886
I'VE READ THE ENTIRE
HARLEQUIN LIBRARY.

28:33.929 --> 28:36.497
I DIDN'T GIVE MY WIFE
THIS SPOON.

28:36.540 --> 28:39.152
NO. A LOVER DID.

28:39.195 --> 28:41.284
A LOVER WHO MURDERED HER
IN A JEALOUS RAGE

28:41.328 --> 28:43.199
BEFORE SHE HAD A CHANCE
TO TELL HIM

28:43.243 --> 28:44.853
THAT SHE WAS LEAVING
HER HUSBAND.

28:44.897 --> 28:48.814
SEE? ENGRAVING SAYS
"A.P. 'HEARTS' N.M."

28:48.857 --> 28:51.904
N.M. IS NORA McQUODDY,
BUT WHO IN THE HELL IS A.P.?

28:51.947 --> 28:53.514
PAPEN IS
A DUTCH NAME.

28:53.557 --> 28:57.779
SCURVY! THERE'S 50 PAPENS
IN THIS COUNTY ALONE.

28:57.823 --> 29:00.173
BUT ONLY ONE AUGUSTUS.

29:00.216 --> 29:03.611
-GUS PAPEN!
-GUS PAPEN. GUS PAPEN.

29:03.654 --> 29:05.395
I THINK I WAS FIRST.

29:08.355 --> 29:10.096
[ NED SIGHS ]

29:10.139 --> 29:11.793
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:11.837 --> 29:14.840
UH, YOUR DAD CAME DOWN,
AND WE HAD A LITTLE...TUSSLE.

29:14.883 --> 29:16.232
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
"A TUSSLE"?

29:16.276 --> 29:17.712
WELL,
MORE LIKE A SCUFFLE.

29:17.756 --> 29:18.931
Charles: CHARLOTTE?

29:18.974 --> 29:19.975
OH, MY GOD.

29:20.019 --> 29:22.282
WAIT.
LET ME EXPLAIN.

29:22.325 --> 29:24.763
OH, MY GOD.

29:24.806 --> 29:25.894
NED, OH, MY GOD.

29:25.938 --> 29:26.939
OHH.

29:26.982 --> 29:27.983
COME HERE.

29:28.027 --> 29:29.332
THE LIGHT...

29:29.376 --> 29:31.117
SO BRIGHT.

29:31.160 --> 29:32.727
ARE YOU OKAY?

29:32.771 --> 29:33.815
MY WRIST.
WHAT?

29:33.859 --> 29:35.861
I THINK
I NEED TO ICE IT.

29:35.904 --> 29:39.125
YOU GO UPSTAIRS,
AND I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

29:39.168 --> 29:42.824
OKAY.

29:42.868 --> 29:44.739
THAT WAS AN ACT!

29:44.783 --> 29:46.219
AN ACT OF FOOLISHNESS.

29:46.262 --> 29:47.829
WHY WOULD YOU BRING HIM
TO THE PIE HOLE?

29:47.873 --> 29:49.222
I DIDN'T.

29:49.265 --> 29:50.658
HE LEFT MY APARTMENT
OF HIS OWN ACCORD,

29:50.701 --> 29:51.877
WANDERED AROUND
FOR AN HOUR,

29:51.920 --> 29:53.226
AND THEN GRABBED A SEAT
AT THE COUNTER.

29:53.269 --> 29:55.054
NO, HE WOULDN'T DO THAT.
HE KNOWS THE RULES.

29:55.097 --> 29:56.359
DIDN'T YOU HEAR?

29:56.403 --> 29:58.144
YOUR DAD'S NOT ONE
FOR CHOCOLATE OR RULES.

29:58.187 --> 29:59.885
SO FROM THIS POINT ON, HE'S
GONNA BE DOING HIS OWN THING.

29:59.928 --> 30:03.540
ALRIGHT, I WILL GO UPSTAIRS,
AND I WILL TALK TO HIM.

30:03.584 --> 30:05.760
WE SAID
WE'D HANDLE THIS TOGETHER.

30:05.804 --> 30:06.848
I'M COMING WITH YOU.

30:06.892 --> 30:08.154
NO.
YOU'RE FAR TOO UPSET.

30:08.197 --> 30:09.459
I'M NOT HAVING YOU
FIGHTING AGAIN.

30:09.503 --> 30:12.027
HE'S A BIG BOY.
HE CAN HANDLE IT.

30:12.071 --> 30:14.856
YEAH, WELL,
MAYBE I CAN'T.

30:14.900 --> 30:16.162
-CHUCK?
-I GET IT.

30:16.205 --> 30:19.208
MY DAD IS STRONG-WILLED,
AND HE'S STUBBORN.

30:19.252 --> 30:20.775
BUT IT'S JUST A NORMAL

30:20.819 --> 30:23.560
FATHER/DAUGHTER/
DAUGHTER'S BOYFRIEND DYNAMIC.

30:23.604 --> 30:24.997
NO, IT'S NOT.

30:25.040 --> 30:26.433
WHY NOT? BECAUSE HE'S BEEN DEAD
FOR 20 YEARS?

30:26.476 --> 30:29.566
JUST...PRETEND
HE'S BEEN IN A COMA.

30:29.610 --> 30:32.004
I DON'T HAVE THE LUXURY OF
PRETENDING THAT HE'S IN A COMA

30:32.047 --> 30:33.875
OR YOU'RE THE HEAD CHEERLEADER
OR ANY OF THIS IS NORMAL,

30:33.919 --> 30:35.442
BECAUSE CHARLES CHARLES
HAS NO PROBLEM

30:35.485 --> 30:37.661
EXPOSING OUR SECRET
TO THE REST OF THE WORLD!

30:37.705 --> 30:40.055
WE NEED TO PUT
A STOP TO THIS.

30:40.099 --> 30:41.883
HOW? 'CAUSE RE-DEADING HIM
IS NOT AN OPTION.

30:41.927 --> 30:44.973
I NEVER SAID THAT. LOOK,
I'VE TRIED EVERYTHING
TO MAKE THIS WORK.

30:45.017 --> 30:49.108
YOU DON'T WANT TO WORK
TOGETHER ANYMORE -- FINE.

30:49.151 --> 30:51.023
YOU TAKE CARE OF IT.

31:06.865 --> 31:08.823
-HI.
-HI.

31:08.867 --> 31:09.911
COME HERE, BUTTON.

31:09.955 --> 31:12.087
WHAT I HAVE HERE
IS A COOKBOOK

31:12.131 --> 31:15.090
OF CULINARY TREASURES
FROM AROUND THE WORLD.

31:15.134 --> 31:17.136
CLOSE YOUR EYES,
TAP THE PAGE,

31:17.179 --> 31:18.615
AND WHERE THE SPOON LANDS

31:18.659 --> 31:20.443
IS WHERE YOU AND I
ARE GONNA GO TONIGHT.

31:20.487 --> 31:22.271
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:22.315 --> 31:24.926
NO, DAD, IT WAS JUST
A MISUNDERSTANDING THAT
WENT OUT OF CONTROL.

31:24.970 --> 31:25.971
LEAVING
IS NOT THE ANSWER.

31:26.014 --> 31:27.450
MM-HMM.

31:27.494 --> 31:29.104
WELL, IS THIS BETTER?
HMM? LET'S SEE.

31:29.148 --> 31:31.933
UH, "RULE 21 -- WHEN CROSSING
ROOMS SIMULTANEOUSLY,

31:31.977 --> 31:33.413
"PARTY 'A' SHALL ANNOUNCE,
'COMING,'

31:33.456 --> 31:35.241
"AT WHICH POINT
PARTY 'B' SHALL PAUSE,

31:35.284 --> 31:38.592
THEN COMMENCE MOVEMENT
WITH THE RESPONSE, 'GOING.'"

31:38.635 --> 31:41.551
THIS IS HOW YOU LIVE?
HUH?

31:41.595 --> 31:44.641
CHARLOTTE, YOU MAY HAVE GROWN UP
WITHOUT ME, BUT I AM BACK,

31:44.685 --> 31:47.122
AND I AM NEVER GONNA STOP
TRYING TO KEEP YOU SAFE.

31:47.166 --> 31:48.863
THE LITTLE GIRL
I LEFT BEHIND

31:48.907 --> 31:51.561
WOULD HAVE NEVER SETTLED
FOR A LOCK-AND-KEY EXISTENCE.

31:51.605 --> 31:53.912
NO, SHE WAS DESTINED
FOR ADVENTURE.

31:53.955 --> 31:56.827
BUT...
MY LIFE IS HERE.

31:56.871 --> 31:59.961
THIS ISN'T A LIFE.
THIS IS A FREAK SHOW.

32:00.005 --> 32:02.181
WE'RE ONLY FREAKS
IN NED'S WORLD.

32:02.224 --> 32:05.575
AWAY FROM NED, WE COULD
DO ANYTHING, BE ANYTHING.

32:09.101 --> 32:12.191
DAD, I JUST WANT THINGS
TO BE HOW THEY USED TO BE.

32:12.234 --> 32:14.236
[ SIGHS ]

32:14.280 --> 32:16.499
COME WITH ME, BUTTON.

32:16.543 --> 32:19.285
PIE IS...SIMPLE.
IT'S LIMITED.

32:19.328 --> 32:24.638
JUST A BIT OF...
PASTRY AND FILLING.

32:24.681 --> 32:26.205
CAKE IS COMPLEX,

32:26.248 --> 32:32.951
LAYERED WITH TREASURES
WAITING TO BE DISCOVERED.

32:32.994 --> 32:34.909
WHICH ONE
DO YOU CHOOSE?

32:42.351 --> 32:44.484
Annabelle:
GUS AND NORA WERE AN ITEM?

32:44.527 --> 32:47.704
COULD HE HAVE HAD
SOMETHING TO DO WITH HER MURDER?

32:47.748 --> 32:49.532
YOU DIDN'T HEAR IT
FROM ME.

32:49.576 --> 32:51.230
OH, MY GOD!

32:51.273 --> 32:52.622
MISS SNOOK,
I ALMOST FORGOT --

32:52.666 --> 32:55.625
I TOLD THE NOTABLE WIDOWS
YOUR STORY,

32:55.669 --> 32:57.932
AND IT MADE US REALIZE
HOW VERY BLESSED WE ARE.

32:57.976 --> 32:59.281
OH.

32:59.325 --> 33:01.892
'TIS BETTER
TO HAVE LOVED AND LOST

33:01.936 --> 33:03.111
THAN TO BE YOU.

33:03.155 --> 33:05.592
WELL,
YOU'LL HAVE TO EXCUSE ME.

33:05.635 --> 33:08.856
I HAVE AN APPOINTMENT
TO GET TO.

33:08.899 --> 33:11.163
TA, SAD MISS SNOOK.

33:11.206 --> 33:13.382
SEE YOU
AT TUESDAY'S POTLUCK.

33:13.426 --> 33:14.905
OH!

33:14.949 --> 33:16.864
NOT ON THE SAVILE ROW
GLEN PLAID CASHMERE.

33:16.907 --> 33:20.215
IT'S JUST PAPIER-MACHE PASTE.
IT'LL COME RIGHT OUT.

33:20.259 --> 33:21.912
SEE YOU AT THE POTLUCK
ON TUESDAY!

33:21.956 --> 33:23.479
TA.

33:23.523 --> 33:25.264
YOU GET ANYTHING
FROM VANDERSLOOP?

33:25.307 --> 33:26.613
JUST A GOOD RILING.

33:26.656 --> 33:28.136
'CAUSE I FOUND SOMETHING,

33:28.180 --> 33:31.966
SNOOPING AROUND
IN GUS PAPEN'S OFFICE.

33:32.010 --> 33:34.621
A PROPOSAL TO REDEVELOP
PAPEN HARBOR LIGHTHOUSE.

33:34.664 --> 33:35.665
MM-HMM.

33:35.709 --> 33:38.146
CHECK THE NEXT PAGE.

33:38.190 --> 33:39.539
OOH! A WATERSLIDE!

33:39.582 --> 33:41.106
HE GOT A GREEN LIGHT.

33:41.149 --> 33:42.890
THE RUNT OF THE PAPEN LITTER
FOUND A WAY TO PROVE

33:42.933 --> 33:45.893
THAT HE CAN GO
TOE-TO-CAPITALISTIC-TOE
WITH ALL HIS BROTHERS.

33:45.936 --> 33:49.244
MERLE'S SUDDEN RETURN
GAVE HIM A McQUODDY TWOFER --

33:49.288 --> 33:51.812
KILL NORA AND THEN
FRAME THE CRAZY CAPTAIN
WITH THE CRIME.

33:51.855 --> 33:53.074
GEEZ.

33:53.118 --> 33:54.771
WITH BOTH OF THEM
OUT OF THE WAY,

33:54.815 --> 33:56.991
HE'S FREE TO REDEVELOP
TO HIS BANK ACCOUNT'S CONTENT,

33:57.035 --> 33:58.688
PROVIDED
HE COULD GET RID OF --

33:58.732 --> 34:00.429
ELLIOT McQUODDY!

34:00.473 --> 34:03.389
CONFIRMING A MEETING WITH GUS
AT THE LIGHTHOUSE TONIGHT.

34:09.395 --> 34:10.657
Elliot: HELP!

34:10.700 --> 34:13.225
[ SCREAMING ]
NO!

34:13.268 --> 34:15.488
-OH, HELL NO!
-OH, HELL NO!

34:15.531 --> 34:18.795
[ SCREAMING ]

34:18.839 --> 34:21.407
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

34:21.450 --> 34:23.713
ALRIGHT, PAPEN!
STEP AWAY FROM THE BOY!

34:23.757 --> 34:24.801
HELP!

34:24.845 --> 34:26.586
IF I DO, HE'LL DIE!

34:26.629 --> 34:29.415
IS THAT REVERSE PSYCHOLOGY?
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT YOU WANT!

34:29.458 --> 34:30.459
Elliot: AAH! HELP!

34:30.503 --> 34:32.287
WHAT I WANT
IS TO SAVE HIM!

34:32.331 --> 34:34.202
IS THAT
REVERSE REVERSE PSYCHOLOGY?

34:34.246 --> 34:35.508
HE DIDN'T DO THIS!

34:35.551 --> 34:37.292
WELL,
THEN WHO THE HELL DID?

34:37.336 --> 34:40.904
Narrator: "WHO THE HELL DID?"
WAS ELLIOT McQUODDY HIMSELF.

34:40.948 --> 34:44.038
REALIZING THE SEVERITY
OF THE IMPENDING NOR'EASTER,

34:44.082 --> 34:47.868
NORA'S SON STRUGGLED
TO DO HIS DEAD MOTHER PROUD

34:47.911 --> 34:49.826
BY RAISING THE SIGNAL FLAGS...

34:51.263 --> 34:52.568
MOMMY!

34:52.612 --> 34:53.830
Narrator: ...AND FAILED.

34:53.874 --> 34:56.572
-THANK YOU.
-IT'S OKAY, ELLIOT.

34:56.616 --> 34:58.139
SO, WAIT A MINUTE.

34:58.183 --> 34:59.662
YOU WEREN'T TRYING
TO WIPE OUT THE McQUODDY LINE

34:59.706 --> 35:01.142
AND TAKE OVER
THIS LIGHTHOUSE?

35:01.186 --> 35:04.145
OF COURSE NOT!
NOT WHEN I WANT TO SAVE IT!

35:04.189 --> 35:06.321
I DON'T LIKE
THE LOOKS OF THIS.

35:06.365 --> 35:08.715
I DON'T LIKE
THE LOOKS OF HIM!

35:15.939 --> 35:20.161
"WELCOME TO THE PAPEN LIGHTHOUSE
RESORT & DAY SPA"?

35:20.205 --> 35:22.163
[ NOTE PLAYS ]

35:22.207 --> 35:23.643
[ FINGERS SNAPPING ]

35:23.686 --> 35:28.604
♪ I'LL BE YOUR CANDLE
ON THE WATER ♪

35:28.648 --> 35:31.259
♪ MY LOVE FOR YOU
WILL ALWAYS BURN ♪

35:31.303 --> 35:32.739
♪ ALWAYS BURN

35:32.782 --> 35:35.742
♪ I KNOW YOU'RE LOST
AND DRIFTING ♪

35:35.785 --> 35:38.614
♪ BUT THE CLOUDS ARE LIFTING

35:38.658 --> 35:40.877
♪ DON'T GIVE UP,
YOU'LL HAVE SOMEWHERE TO -- ♪

35:40.921 --> 35:42.879
SHUT THE A CAPPELLA UP.

35:42.923 --> 35:45.839
AND THAT'S HOW
OUR COCKTAIL HOUR BEGINS --

35:45.882 --> 35:46.970
WITH A BANG AND A SONG!

35:47.014 --> 35:48.407
FOLLOWED BY
A GOURMET MEAL

35:48.450 --> 35:50.278
AND DANCING
HERE IN THE LAMP ROOM.

35:50.322 --> 35:53.238
THAT'S WHY I CALLED ELLIOT --
TO PITCH HIM!

35:53.281 --> 35:55.936
THIS FEELS
REALLY, REALLY WRONG.

35:55.979 --> 35:58.721
HOW CAN A SYMBOL OF LOVE
BE WRONG?

35:58.765 --> 36:01.637
SO, YOU...
AND MY MOM?

36:01.681 --> 36:05.467
SHE WANTED TO TELL YOU.
THEN YOUR FATHER RETURNED.

36:05.511 --> 36:07.034
WE TRIED TO PUT
OUR FEELINGS ASIDE,

36:07.077 --> 36:10.080
TO GIVE THEM A SHOT
AT RECAPTURING THE PAST...

36:10.124 --> 36:11.821
BUT THEY COULDN'T.

36:11.865 --> 36:14.302
LET'S HAVE SOMETHING GOOD
COME OUT OF THIS TRAGEDY.

36:14.346 --> 36:18.480
OH, IF THAT'S THE PLAN,
PLEASE NIX THE GLITTER.

36:18.524 --> 36:21.222
WHO'D YOU GET TO
DECORATE THE PLACE --
ANNABELLE VANDERSLOOP?

36:21.266 --> 36:22.354
Emerson:
WAIT A MINUTE.

36:22.397 --> 36:24.573
WHAT IF CRAZY CRAFT LADY
WAS UP HERE,

36:24.617 --> 36:26.401
BUT INSTEAD
OF A HOT-GLUE GUN,

36:26.445 --> 36:28.403
SHE BROUGHT
A STONE-COLD HARPOON?

36:28.447 --> 36:30.797
MRS. VANDERSLOOP WAS
MY MOTHER'S BEST FRIEND.

36:30.840 --> 36:31.972
WHY WOULD SHE KILL HER?

36:32.015 --> 36:34.409
BECAUSE NORA
WASN'T THE ONLY SQUEEZE

36:34.453 --> 36:37.151
PAPEN HERE WAS SQUEEZIN'.

36:37.195 --> 36:40.154
TURN AROUND THERE,
SHORTSTOP.

36:40.198 --> 36:42.069
Olive: [ GASPS ]
PAPIER-MACHE!

36:42.112 --> 36:44.898
YOU WERE GETTING DOWN
WITH THE DIORAMA DAME.

36:44.941 --> 36:47.422
I DAMNED THAT DAME EVERY TIME
SHE MADE AN ADVANCE --

36:47.466 --> 36:51.034
LIKE TONIGHT, IN MY OFFICE,
AND A DOZEN NIGHTS BEFORE.

36:51.078 --> 36:52.427
COME ON, PAPEN.

36:52.471 --> 36:54.386
YOU TWO MUST HAVE BEEN
SWAPPING SOMETHING

36:54.429 --> 36:56.388
OTHER THAN
HISTORICAL FACTOIDS.

36:56.431 --> 36:58.955
ONCE...YEARS AGO...

36:58.999 --> 37:01.044
AT THE HISTORICAL SOCIETY
CHRISTMAS PARTY.

37:01.088 --> 37:03.569
SO, SPURNED LOVER
SPEARS HER BEST FRIEND,

37:03.612 --> 37:06.963
THEN FRAMES GHOST HUSBAND
TO TAKE THE FALL.

37:07.007 --> 37:10.053
LET'S RUBBER-CEMENT HER ASS
TO A PRISON BED.

37:13.318 --> 37:17.322
OH, TELL ME YOU GUYS
ARE MISSING A BARITONE.

37:17.365 --> 37:18.540
OH!

37:18.584 --> 37:20.238
A FULL HOUSE!

37:20.281 --> 37:23.458
SO MUCH FOR KEEPING
THE INNOCENT-VICTIM COUNT DOWN.

37:23.502 --> 37:26.069
SERIOUSLY,
DOES SHE TOOT GLITTER?

37:26.113 --> 37:27.506
OH, THAT AIN'T GLITTER.

37:27.549 --> 37:28.855
THAT'S GUNPOWDER.

37:28.898 --> 37:30.117
Elliot:
SHE'S GOING TO BLOW US UP.

37:30.160 --> 37:32.598
YOU REMEMBER
MY HUSBAND, ADOLPH,

37:32.641 --> 37:34.208
THE MUNITIONS MANUFACTURER?

37:34.252 --> 37:36.471
I INHERITED
THE REMAINING INVENTORY.

37:36.515 --> 37:38.604
SAID I'D SAVE IT
FOR A RAINY DAY.

37:38.647 --> 37:41.911
AND LOOK -- IT'S HERE!

37:41.955 --> 37:43.522
ANNABELLE, WHY?

37:43.565 --> 37:46.264
YOU TOSSED OUR LOVE ASIDE
LIKE IT NEVER HAPPENED!

37:46.307 --> 37:47.743
IT WAS ONE NIGHT!

37:47.787 --> 37:49.267
WHAT WE HAD
WAS SO MUCH MORE SPECIAL

37:49.310 --> 37:50.790
THAN ANYTHING YOU HAD
WITH NORA.

37:50.833 --> 37:53.314
WHEN MERLE RETURNED,
IT WAS THE ANSWER TO MY PRAYERS.

37:53.358 --> 37:55.403
BUT EVEN THEN,
YOU COULDN'T LET GO!

37:55.447 --> 37:57.623
SO I HAD TO
ELIMINATE HER.

37:57.666 --> 37:59.538
I STILL LOVE NORA.

37:59.581 --> 38:02.323
SHUT UP.

38:02.367 --> 38:04.107
THAT'S WHY
YOU'VE LEFT ME NO CHOICE.

38:04.151 --> 38:07.589
I DON'T UNDERSTAND HOW KILLING
US IS GONNA SOLVE ANYTHING!

38:07.633 --> 38:09.243
I DO! I DO!

38:09.287 --> 38:11.637
UM, WHEN YOU CALLED ME
"SAD MISS SNOOK,"

38:11.680 --> 38:13.639
OH, IT REALLY
HONKED ME OFF,

38:13.682 --> 38:16.250
BUT NOW I REALIZE THAT
YOU RECOGNIZED SADNESS IN ME

38:16.294 --> 38:18.426
BECAUSE YOU HAD IT
IN YOU.

38:18.470 --> 38:21.255
UH, THE REST OF YOU
DON'T KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE

38:21.299 --> 38:23.562
TO KNOW IN YOUR HEART
THAT YOU BELONG WITH SOMEBODY,

38:23.605 --> 38:25.564
IF YOU COULD ONLY ELIMINATE
EVERYBODY ELSE

38:25.607 --> 38:27.914
SO THAT MAYBE
HE'D FINALLY, FINALLY GRASP

38:27.957 --> 38:29.916
WHAT YOU'VE BEEN TRYING
TO SHOW HIM --

38:29.959 --> 38:32.179
THAT FEELING THAT YOU'VE BEEN
DYING TO RECAPTURE.

38:32.222 --> 38:33.702
IF ONLY FOR A MOMENT.

38:33.746 --> 38:35.356
BUT THAT MOMENT NEVER COMES,
SO WHAT DO YOU DO?

38:35.400 --> 38:36.401
DECIDE NOT TO LOVE NED?

38:36.444 --> 38:38.490
-GUS.
-GUS! GUS!

38:38.533 --> 38:39.534
SEE? I'VE TRIED THAT.

38:39.578 --> 38:40.883
-ME TOO!
-DID IT WORK?

38:40.927 --> 38:42.320
-HECK NO.
-HECK NO!

38:42.363 --> 38:44.017
SO YOU KNOW WHAT I SAY?

38:44.060 --> 38:45.366
[ BLOWS ]

38:45.410 --> 38:48.326
Narrator: ANNABELLE VANDERSLOOP
DID MOVE ON.

38:48.369 --> 38:52.330
SHE WAS NO LONGER SAD
ABOUT LOSING GUS' LOVE,

38:52.373 --> 38:53.983
SINCE A 30-YEAR PRISON SENTENCE

38:54.027 --> 38:57.247
GAVE HER SOMETHING
TO BE TRULY SAD ABOUT.

38:57.291 --> 39:00.250
MERLE AND ELLIOT McQUODDY
MOVED ON, AS WELL,

39:00.294 --> 39:03.515
BECOMING PARTNERS
IN GUS PAPEN'S LIGHTHOUSE HOTEL.

39:03.558 --> 39:07.562
THEY USED THE PROFITS
FOR A TRIP AROUND THE WORLD

39:07.606 --> 39:09.216
AND FOUND, ON THE HIGH SEAS,

39:09.259 --> 39:12.001
THE ROUTE BACK
TO THEIR FATHER/SON BOND.

39:12.045 --> 39:14.743
MEANWHILE,
PRIVATE DETECTIVE EMERSON COD

39:14.787 --> 39:16.963
WAS AFLOAT
IN A SEA OF REWARD MONEY,

39:17.006 --> 39:20.140
GIVEN BY THE PAPEN COUNTY
HISTORICAL SOCIETY,

39:20.183 --> 39:24.013
WHICH HE SHARED WITH
THE JUNIOR P.I. IN TRAINING.

39:24.057 --> 39:25.275
NICE WORK, SNOOK.

39:25.319 --> 39:27.756
THANKS, COD.
I LEARNED FROM THE BEST.

39:27.800 --> 39:30.498
WAIT. HOLD ON, NOW.
WE AIN'T DONE.

39:30.542 --> 39:35.416
YOU REMEMBER WHEN YOU SAID
YOU WERE STILL IN LOVE WITH NED?

39:35.460 --> 39:38.680
THAT WASN'T JUST FOR
WICKED WIDOW'S BENEFIT, WAS IT?

39:38.724 --> 39:40.334
NO.

39:40.378 --> 39:43.511
OH, EMERSON, I THOUGHT
I'D STOMPED OUT THAT FLAME,

39:43.555 --> 39:46.601
OR AT LEAST BROUGHT IT DOWN
TO A SMOLDER, BUT NO.

39:46.645 --> 39:49.952
I STILL BURN AND YEARN FOR HIM
NOW MORE THAN EVER.

39:49.996 --> 39:50.997
MM-HMM.

39:51.040 --> 39:52.694
DO I NEED TO BE
CONCERNED

39:52.738 --> 39:55.044
THAT ANY OF MY PIE HOLE PEEPS
ARE GONNA BE ELIMINATED?

39:55.088 --> 39:57.177
MEANING,
AM I GONNA HARPOON CHUCK

39:57.220 --> 40:00.441
SO NED
WILL FINALLY LOVE ME?

40:00.485 --> 40:01.660
NO.

40:01.703 --> 40:03.531
WELL...

40:03.575 --> 40:05.011
IF THE DAY FINALLY COMES

40:05.054 --> 40:07.883
THAT BEING AROUND PIE BOY
AND HIS PIE GIRL

40:07.927 --> 40:09.842
MAKE YOUR SUFFERING
INSUFFERABLE,

40:09.885 --> 40:12.497
I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT, UH,

40:12.540 --> 40:14.063
THERE'S A PLACE FOR YOU,

40:14.107 --> 40:17.110
RIGHT HERE IN THIS
PROFESSIONAL ESTABLISHMENT.

40:17.153 --> 40:18.241
[ SNIP ]

40:18.285 --> 40:19.852
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS ASK.

40:19.895 --> 40:21.941
EMERSON COD.

40:21.984 --> 40:24.857
I THINK I MAY BE
WINNING YOU OVER.

40:24.900 --> 40:26.902
ITTY-BITTY...

40:26.946 --> 40:29.731
YOU MADE ME
LOVE A RAINY DAY AGAIN.

40:29.775 --> 40:31.385
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:35.302 --> 40:37.391
Chuck:
YOU'VE GOT TO UNDERSTAND.

40:37.435 --> 40:41.439
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE GIRL,
I USED TO COMPARE MY DAD

40:41.482 --> 40:44.267
TO ALL THE OTHER DADS
ON OUR STREET.

40:44.311 --> 40:46.052
I PROBABLY WASN'T
VERY OBJECTIVE,

40:46.095 --> 40:47.445
BECAUSE I WAS CONVINCED

40:47.488 --> 40:49.490
THAT HE WAS
THE STRONGEST AND BRAVEST

40:49.534 --> 40:51.361
AND MOST FUN MAN
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

40:51.405 --> 40:54.234
I CAN SAY, OBJECTIVELY,
HE WAS ALL THOSE THINGS.

40:54.277 --> 40:56.932
AND WHEN HE WAS GONE,
THAT'S HOW I REMEMBERED HIM.

40:56.976 --> 41:00.588
I PUT HIM
ON A PATERNAL PEDESTAL.

41:00.632 --> 41:02.590
AND NOW...

41:02.634 --> 41:04.505
NOW HE WANTS ME
TO LEAVE.

41:04.549 --> 41:06.289
LEAVE? WHERE?

41:06.333 --> 41:08.161
ANYWHERE
THE SPOON LANDS.

41:08.204 --> 41:09.728
HE PROMISED ME
AN ADVENTURE

41:09.771 --> 41:12.818
LIKE THE ONES HE TOLD ME ABOUT
WHEN I WAS A KID.

41:12.861 --> 41:15.298
ALL I HAVE TO DO IS...

41:15.342 --> 41:17.170
CHOOSE CAKE OVER PIE.

41:17.213 --> 41:18.824
OH.

41:18.867 --> 41:21.130
HE'S TRYING TO BE THE DAD
THAT I ALWAYS DREAMED OF,

41:21.174 --> 41:26.832
SOMEONE WHO COULD KEEP
HIS LITTLE GIRL SAFE AND HAPPY.

41:26.875 --> 41:29.530
EXCEPT I'M...

41:29.574 --> 41:31.967
I'M NOT A LITTLE GIRL.

41:32.011 --> 41:36.363
WHICH IS WHY I TOLD HIM
THE SPOON LANDS HERE.

41:36.406 --> 41:39.409
I ALREADY FEEL SAFE
AND HAPPY, AND...

41:39.453 --> 41:42.804
AND, BESIDES,
WE HAVE ADVENTURES EVERY DAY.

41:42.848 --> 41:45.459
WHAT DID HE THINK
OF YOUR DECISION?

41:45.503 --> 41:47.069
HE'S WAITING FOR YOU
UPSTAIRS.

41:47.113 --> 41:49.115
WITH A GUN?

41:49.158 --> 41:50.769
WITH AN APOLOGY.

41:50.812 --> 41:53.511
HE WANTS US ALL
TO START FRESH.

41:53.554 --> 41:55.687
THEN HE'S A GOOD DAD.

41:55.730 --> 41:57.645
MM-HMM.

41:57.689 --> 41:58.951
AND YOU'RE A GOOD MAN.

41:58.994 --> 42:00.735
[ CHUCKLES ]

42:01.910 --> 42:03.346
COME ON.

42:03.390 --> 42:04.522
[ CHUCKLES ]

42:05.784 --> 42:06.872
DAD?

42:06.915 --> 42:08.656
COME ON!
GRAB YOUR HAT!

42:08.700 --> 42:11.311
WE'RE TAKING HOT TODDIES UP
TO THE ROOF TO WATCH THE SNOW!

42:15.097 --> 42:16.446
CHUCK?

42:18.057 --> 42:19.493
NO!

42:19.537 --> 42:21.103
DAD!
